description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, accurate, efficient and self-motivated individual to join our friendly professional team in the busy Cytotoxic Chemotherapy Production Unit at the City Hospital campus.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This interesting and varied role will require you to process and manufacture a wide range of cytotoxic chemotherapy, monoclonal antibodies, antibiotics and clinical trial preparations. The work will be varied and challenging, working to tight schedules to achieve targets and responding to customer needs and deadlines. Therefore, you should be able work under pressure, to prioritise and organise workloads and be able to work alone or as part of a bigger team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will contribute towards an efficiently run unit, maintaining and improving our service to patients. We are looking for confident, self-motivated individuals with excellent IT, communication, problem solving and decision making skills.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be required to learn all aspects of this challenging role which includes aseptic manufacturing, maintenance of equipment/facilities, clerical and stock control duties.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be: flexible; required to work shifts by rota (including evenings, weekends and bank holidays); committed to hospital Pharmacy; enthusiastic; adaptable to change and ready for a challenge.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Previous experience in aseptic production and dispensing is desirable but there will be full training in all aspects of aseptic cytotoxic manufacture provided for suitable candidates.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A few permanent positions are available for a Senior Pharmacy Assistant Technical Officer (37.5 hours).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be in possession of NVQ Level 2 Pharmacy Services or an equivalent Pharmacy Manufacturing qualification to work as Band 3. If you are working towards this or need to undertake this qualification, successful applicant will be a Band 2 until qualification is gained.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a committed, forward-thinking individual looking to join a dynamic team we look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameFarzana KhalidJob titleChief Technician – Cytotoxic Chemotherapy Production UnitEmail addressfarzana.khalid@nuh.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Farzana Khalid (Chief Technician) via e-mail farzana.khalid@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
